entries.summary: The Jasmine Revolution in Tunisia led to the ousting of President Zine el-Abidine Ben Ali, ending his 23-year reign and forcing him into exile.
The Muslim Brotherhood in Egypt urged its followers to protest after Friday prayers, marking the first time in the latest wave of unrest that the group has made such a call.

Two men charged in the death of a Chicago teen who performed at an inauguration event. Carnival Triumph cruise ship being towed to Mobile, AL after experiencing a fire in the engine room. Speculation arises about the possibility of the next pope being from Africa or Latin America.
